An '''Infinity Wave''' was a [[Superweapon/Legends|superweapon]] invented by the [[Kwa/Legends|Kwa]].

==Description==
Through the 'power of the cosmos' harnessed by the [[Kwa/Legends|Kwa]] [[Infinity Gate]]s, it was possible to direct enormous waves of energy presumably anywhere in the [[Galaxy/Legends|Galaxy]]. Such a wave was able to suck an entire [[Planet/Legends|planet]], along with surrounding satellites, into infinity, presumably unmaking all life and destroying all matter. As a side-effect, [[Hyperspace/Legends|hyperspace]] navigation in the entire [[Sector/Legends|sector]] where the Wave hit became impossible.

In [[31 BBY/Legends|31 BBY]] a [[Nightsisters/Legends|Nightsister]] clan mother, [[Zalem/Legends|Zalem]], triggered an infinity wave from the [[Infinity Gate]] located in the [[Star Temple]] on [[Dathomir/Legends|Dathomir]]. She aimed the wave at [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]], intending to wipe out the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]] and the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Republic]] capital at the same time. Her plan was thwarted by [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]] [[Quinlan Vos/Legends|Quinlan Vos]] who had been appointed as the Temple Guardian. Vos reversed the wave and directed it back at its source, which destroyed the Infinity Gate in the resulting explosion.

